How to Upgrade Pve7.4 to Pve8 Last night, When I found that proxmox ve 8 has been released. Then I want to try it and I do it immediately. Here is what I did to upgrade pve.
1 Backup 1.2 backup vms and containers &ndash;skip&ndash;
1.2 Backup /etc/ folder &ndash;skip&ndash;
Check upgrade status 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 # Upgrade to latest pve 7.4 apt update &amp;&amp; apt -y dist-upgrade # Reboot systemctl reboot # pve7to8 checklist script pve7to8 --full Change Sourcelist for debian 12 1 2 3 4 5 # Backup debian 11 sourcelist mv /etc/apt/sources.

##How to let a new server join the exist HCI cluster
1. Insall the pve on the server &ndash;skip&mdash;
2. Let the new server join the pve cluster 1 2 #ssh login the server pvecm add 10.32.4.37 3. configure NTP server 1 2 3 4 5 cat &gt;&gt; /etc/systemd/timesyncd.conf &lt;&lt; EOF NTP=192.168.0.2 192.168.0.3 EOF # Restart systemd-timesyncd service to apply settings systemctl restart systemd-timesyncd 4. Install ceph 1 pveceph install 5.
